OL,5, Nigeria says it wants primary school   
OL,6, teachers to conduct lessons in local   
OL,7, languages instead of English, which is 
OL,8, currently used. But how practical is   
OL,9, that in a country where more than 600  
OL,10, different tongues are spoken?          
OL,12,FKareem Abiodun Habeebullah, whose      
OL,13,Fmother tongue is Yoruba, was just a    
OL,14,Fsecondary school student when he was   
OL,15,Fwhipped in class for not speaking in   
OL,16,FEnglish.                               
OL,19,F"I know the answer but I can only      
OL,20,Frespond with my mother language," he   
OL,21,Fremembers saying.                      
